1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,000
ControlX is a local-first proof console for authorized Web research.
Find the delta. Prove the impact.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:22,000
This local demo uses two synthetic accounts, controlled objects,
and a four-request ceiling.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Each account contributes its own DevTools cURL capture.
Tokens, object IDs, URLs, markers, and bodies stay ephemeral.

4
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:46,000
ControlX confirms one changed object locator, two distinct sessions,
and a redacted request preview before any traffic is sent.

5
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:59,000
The matrix runs B→B, A→A, then B→A by changing only the session.
Exposure stops immediately; stable denials close only the tested branch.

6
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:12,000
The receipt preserves hashes, outcomes, timing, network controls,
and integrity metadata. Optional AI review cannot control the verdict.

7
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Built in Codex with GPT-5.6 Sol.
ControlX: Find the delta. Prove the impact.
